{"id":27037,"date":"2019-01-15T15:55:49","date_gmt":"2019-01-15T11:55:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=27037"},"modified":"2019-05-23T13:45:41","modified_gmt":"2019-05-23T09:45:41","slug":"ibn-abbas-three-not-without","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/01\/15\/ibn-abbas-three-not-without\/","title":{"rendered":"Ibn Abbas on Deeds: Three deeds not accepted without three others"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Al-Saffarini reported: Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThree verses were revealed in connection with three others. One will not be accepted without its counterpart. First, the verse, \u2018<strong>Establish prayer and give charity<\/strong>,\u2019 (2:43). Whoever prays and does not give charity, his prayer is not accepted. Second, the saying of the Almighty, \u2018<strong>Be grateful to me and your parents<\/strong>,\u2019 (31:14). Whoever is grateful to Allah and is not grateful to his parents, it will not be accepted from him. Third, the saying of the Almighty, \u201c<strong>Obey Allah and obey the messenger<\/strong>,\u2019 (3:32). Whoever obeys Allah and does not obey the messenger, it will not be accepted from him.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Ghidh\u0101\u2019 al-Alb\u0101b 1\/392<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0641\u0627\u0631\u064a\u0646\u064a \u0648\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0633\u064d \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u062b\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u062b\u064f \u0622\u064a\u064e\u0627\u062a\u064d \u0646\u064e\u0632\u064e\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0645\u064e\u0642\u0652\u0631\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0628\u0650\u062b\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u062b\u0650 \u0622\u064a\u064e\u0627\u062a\u064d \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u